Package: satin2
Type: Package
Title: Functions for reading and displaying ocean data derived from satellites for oceanographic applications
Version: 0.1
Date: 2020-09-20
Encoding: UTF-8
Author: Héctor Villalobos and Eduardo González-Rodríguez <egonzale@cicese.mx>
Maintainer: Héctor Villalobos <hvillalo@ipn.mx>
Description: Main functions import a user defined subset of ocean data from nc or hdf5 files. Visualisations and further analysis of satellite derived ocean data can be produced. Currently supported NOAA products includes: Moderate-resolution Imaging Spectroradiometer (from Aqua satellite: MODIS-Aqua) and Sea-viewing Wide Field-of-view Sensor (SeaWiFS). Also, The functions have been tested with sea surface temperature (SST), chlorophyll-a (Chl-a) concentration and net ocean primary production from Oregon State University. 
Depends: R (>= 3.5.0)
License: GPL-3
URL: https://github.com/hvillalo/satin2
BugReports: https://github.com/hvillalo/satin2/issues
Collate: satin-class.R read.cmems.R read.ghrsst.R read.nasaoc.R read.osunpp.R
         fmainPos.R imageScale.R plot.satin.R satinPalette.R quiver.R
         verticalProfiles.R satinDataframe.R pixelate.R climatology.R crop.R
         extractPts.R isolines.R satinMean.R anomaly.R
Imports:
